The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to clustering and graph partitioning, which are central topics in computer science. The use of parameterized algorithms and the focus on specific objective functions suggest that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem is also related to correlation clustering, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and the use of graph theory suggests cs.GT (Graph Theory) as another possible category. Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and algorithm design suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category as well.
